Review: I had to fill in some gaps, but my interpretation of the story is as follows.  The story starts off reasonably enough, and any office drone can certainly relate, with someone who is tired of their work routine and tries to rebel by creating a genuine emotional connection with a co-worker.  In a Kafkaesque twist, the soulless bureaucracy of the office stamps out genuine human interaction by promptly firing both offenders.  The story does not end well for the protagonist, but it did entertain me and make me think, so I consider it high "valence" for the careful reader.
